Generic single-database configuration.

## First-time production deploy (REQUIRED for existing Render deployment)

If the Render PostgreSQL database was created before Alembic was added (before
the "add Alembic migration infrastructure" commit), the tables already exist but
Alembic doesn't know about them. Run this ONCE in the Render console before
deploying:

    alembic stamp 63d647e9a78b

Then redeploy. The startup lifespan will run `alembic upgrade head` and apply
only the new migrations (lots/records and price_markup_pct).

For a brand-new Render deployment (empty database), no stamp needed — all
migrations run in order automatically.
